extract_nfsA_sequences.py

Reads a Panaroo gene_presence_absence.csv, finds all nfsA-related gene clusters,
extracts locus tags per isolate, and pulls protein sequences from per-isolate FAA files.

Submit to SLURM:
  sbatch extract_nfsA_sequences.py \
      --presence_absence /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/panaroo_resultsL_RO/gene_presence_absence.csv \
      --faa_dir /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/bakta_resultsL \
      --output_dir /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/nfsA_output

Run interactively:
  python3 extract_nfsA_sequences.py \
      --presence_absence /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/panaroo_resultsL_RO/gene_presence_absence.csv \
      --faa_dir /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/bakta_resultsL \
      --output_dir /mnt/shared/scratch/hhocking/nfsA_output

Arguments:
  --presence_absence  Path to Panaroo gene_presence_absence.csv  [required]
  --faa_dir           Directory containing per-isolate FAA files  [required]
  --faa_ext           FAA file extension (default: .faa)
  --gene_name         Gene name to search for (default: nfsA)
  --output_dir        Output directory [required]

Outputs:
  <gene>_all_sequences.faa       All extracted sequences
  <gene>_locus_tag_summary.tsv   Per-isolate locus tag and length summary
  <gene>_missing_isolates.txt    Isolates absent from all matching clusters
  <gene>_sequence_not_found.txt  Locus tags not found in FAA files
"""

